title: NY Space: Seena Sleem, Bayside soccer
text:
Pace for News MY VITALS
Height: 5-1
Weight: 108
Age: 17
Class: Senior
MY RESUME
Played for the varsity as a freshman and has tallied 28 goals and 25 assists at Bayside . Scored a goal against Susan Wagner in the 'A' playoff bracket final last year to help lead the Commodores to a 3-1 victory.
MY FAVORITES
Movie: Moulin Rouge
"I've seen it so many times, it's not even funny. I love musicals, I love the whole romance kind of thing."
Food: Pasta and noodles
"Anything with carbs. I like lo mein, fettucine alfredo, anything like that."
TV Show: One Tree Hill
"I feel like I can really relate to it, there's a lot of voice-over which I really like. It's really well done, and the plot is really interesting."
Dream Date: Orlando Bloom
"I've had a crush on him since sixth grade. If I went out with him I would pass out or something."
Role Models: My parents
"Definitely my parents. They are the ones who taught me all my morals that I live by today, they've supported me, and I look up to them so much."
Music: Paramore
"They are just really catchy. I'm a lyric kind of girl, so I'm really into their lyrics. The lead singer is a female, and I'm really into that."
Holiday: Christmas
"That's the one where you get presents and you get to spend time with your family, so it's the best."
Dream Car: Mercedes convertible
"I've always wanted one, in silver or red. I would love to drive with the top down and cruise to the beach."
MY Quote: ON THIS YEAR'S BAYSIDE SQUAD
"I think, since it's a brand new team, it's a new experience, and it's fun. It's a challenge playing with people who I haven't played with before. I moved to sweeper this year from left midfield, so that's also been an adjustment. It's getting easier though."
